# Push new build (building-map-explorer)

When the user asks to push, deploy, publish, or sync code to the live site:

## Remember

- **Live site builds from GitHub `main`**, not uncommitted local files. Same version stamp can still differ if local code was not pushed.
- **Never commit** `.env.local` or `deploy-bundle.json`.

## Standard code push (app UI + repo JSON)

1. `git pull origin main` (Settings sync may have committed on remote)
2. `npm run lint && npm run typecheck && npm run test`
3. `git status` — review changes; stage only intended files
4. `git commit -m "…"` with a clear message
5. `git push origin main` → triggers `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` (R2 JSON upload + build + GitHub Pages)

## Map data + pictures (no code deploy needed)

Settings → **Sync to Cloudflare & GitHub** (runs `sync-deploy.yml`). User should hard-refresh after ~2 minutes.

## After push to main

- Watch: https://github.com/quadreal-r/building-map-explorer/actions
- Live: https://quadreal-r.github.io/building-map-explorer/
- Hard-refresh when deploy finishes (~5–10 min)
- Optional: Actions → **Manual deploy (commit, push & Pages)** for an explicit Pages deploy + version bump

## Documents / R2 extras (when changed)

```powershell
npm run upload-rtu-documents-r2 -- --from-folder "…" --all-files --skip-existing
npm run upload-json-to-r2
```

Requires `VITE_RTU_DOCUMENTS_BASE_URL` in GitHub secrets for document links online.

## User shortcut phrase

If they say **"Everything is good now, push the code"**: pull, test, commit, push to `main`, report Actions URL.

